<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Self Hosting on Ronak Vanpariya</title><link>https://vanpariyar.in/tags/self-hosting/</link><description>Recent content in Self Hosting on Ronak Vanpariya</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 21 Oct 2024 23:14:11 +0530</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://vanpariyar.in/tags/self-hosting/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>How to Self-Host WordPress Playground on GitHub Pages with a Custom Domain</title><link>https://vanpariyar.in/blog/how-to-self-host-wordpress-playground-on-github-pages-with-a-custom-domain/</link><pubDate>Mon, 21 Oct 2024 23:14:11 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://vanpariyar.in/blog/how-to-self-host-wordpress-playground-on-github-pages-with-a-custom-domain/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Hello 👋&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this post, we&amp;rsquo;ll explore how to self-host a WordPress Playground on GitHub Pages. This is a fun and educational project that not only saves bandwidth for WordPress servers but also allows you to showcase your product on a custom domain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-self-host-wordpress-playground"&gt;Why Self-Host WordPress Playground?
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;WordPress Playground primarily uses static files and runs directly in the user&amp;rsquo;s browser. By self-hosting it on GitHub Pages, you can save bandwidth on WordPress servers and provide a unique experience by using your custom domain. This is especially useful if you want to demo your product or create a personalized WordPress Playground instance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-self-host-wordpress-playground"&gt;How to Self-Host WordPress Playground
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;To get started, follow these steps:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-fork-the-wordpress-playground-repository"&gt;1. Fork the WordPress Playground Repository
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;First, fork the WordPress Playground repository from &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/WordPress/wordpress-playground" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
 &gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt;. This will create a copy of the repository under your GitHub account.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="2-create-a-github-actions-workflow"&gt;2. Create a GitHub Actions Workflow
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Next, you&amp;rsquo;ll need to set up a GitHub Actions workflow to deploy the playground to GitHub Pages. Create a new workflow file, for example:&lt;/p&gt;
